  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong>&nbsp;basmati rice</strong> and 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> <strong>water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/720.step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/720.step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/720.step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/720.step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/720.step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p>\r\n<p>Zest the <strong>lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter!</p>\r\n<p>Roll the<strong>&nbsp;</strong>zested<strong> lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice!) and cut in half</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/720.step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/720.step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/720.step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/720.step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/720.step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine&nbsp;the <strong>chopped&nbsp;</strong><strong>ginger</strong>, <strong>lime zest</strong>, juice of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lime</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>toasted</strong>&nbsp;<strong>sesame oil</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, a splash of <strong>water</strong> and 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]&nbsp;</span><strong>sugar</strong> (preferably brown)</p>\r\n<p>Mix everything together thoroughly - this is your <strong>teriyaki sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/720.step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/720.step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/720.step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/720.step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/720.step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and grate the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Slice the <strong>sugar snap peas</strong> and the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> very finely</p>\r\n<p>Mix the <strong>grated carrot</strong>, <strong>snap peas</strong> and <strong>spring onion</strong> together in a bowl with the<strong> rice wine vinegar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;- this is your<strong> snap pea slaw</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/720.step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/720.step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/720.step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/720.step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/720.step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a&nbsp;large pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once&nbsp;hot, add the <strong>pork</strong><strong>&nbsp;strips</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 3-5 min or until it's starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/720.step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/720.step-5-x400.jpg",
